VII. THE DANICA LYNCHPIN (the braid that makes it inevitable)
=====================================================================
Once the party knows they need the TRUE Eldergleam, they have NO WAY to find
it without the chosen sisters of Kynareth — and the road runs through DANICA.
  THE SECRET: the true heart's location is the chosen sisters' deepest secret.
    NO MAN EVER may know — not Krusp, not Galmar, not the male priests. A
    women's-mystery secret. Three living chosen sisters: DANICA, one in
    WHITERUN (the cold temple), and one VISITING SOLITUDE (working the slow
    node). Danica KNOWS the location herself.
  THE WALL: the Whiterun temple is COLD to the Lanterns — Danica wrote her
    sisters of the cloth about her heartbreak, warning them not to leave the
    vow because "the other side is bleak." Her grief became the temple's
    cautionary tale about the party.
  THE BRAID: the apology that slows Davinia's Crown (Winter Ledger re-
    anchoring), the officiant Path 3 needs, and the ONLY guide to the heart
    are ONE WOMAN, ONE RECONCILIATION. Danica is no longer just Davinia's
    personal subplot — she is the GATEKEEPER TO THE MAIN-PLOT CURE.
  [GM TBD: develop the Solitude chosen sister as an NPC — someone the party
   could meet, and the Solitude node as a STILL-STANDING node they could
   DEFEND as a win.]

=====================================================================
VIII. SAVING NODES (the standing open door)
=====================================================================
EVERY node is SAVEABLE. The party simply keeps not going. Every FUTURE node
is the same — all saveable, the chances recurring. The front falls because
they are BUSY; that neglect is the standing tragedy AND a door that never
closes. Offer node-defense opportunities on the road from here on (a dying
grove, a firewall about to fall); let them win some if they choose, and let
the ones they skip fall and be felt later. The Solitude node (slow, strong,
a chosen sister already there) is the best first candidate for a savable win.

