IX. SUPPORTING BEATS
=====================================================================
THE GREYBEARDS (the monastery): they hold the summit against the corruption
  by Voice alone, exhausted. They will not come down. Reaching them opens the
  Way of the Voice, hands the party the word TOWER, and advances the Bjorn-
  Dragonborn question — but they CANNOT name a Dragonborn (no one can); if
  Bjorn is even present (he should not be), they perceive nothing nameable.
  They see divine claims on mortals: Hircine's brand on Ylva, the stag's
  attention on Saijah. One quiet beat at the door.
VARON: follows Saijah up the Stair; he WITNESSES the escalation (the god's
  interest, the senses, the rivalry) — NOT a resolved choice. The report-home
  beat still triggers (he saw a god court the Colony's released sister); what
  he writes or falsifies is his. The four-hander RESOLUTION is a LATER scene.
MILA: the Steps are no place for her; who argues for leaving her where, and
  with whom, is a free scene (Saijah close, Ylva far, Bjorn the default).
REWARD (Section 5): Way of the Voice opened; a Word of Power; Bjorn-question
  advanced; the Throat STAUNCHED not sealed (a finger cut, not the body —
  echoing Darkwater). Gaelen escaped. The party LEAVES KNOWING the main plot.
CONSEQUENCE IF IGNORED (per gate 3): Dagon corrupts the Throat, the Time-Wound
  widens, the Greybeards fall, the Way of the Voice closes, Saijah's migraine
  becomes permanent and worsening. The most cosmically dangerous fire to leave
  burning.

